Program: Outlook
Title: 15/02/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00nl1qt
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 16 Feb 2012
The mother and son who were photographed in the aftermath of protests in Yemen last October tell us the story behind the award-winning image. Also, the Indian grandfather who walks the streets of Delhi collecting donations of unused medicines to pass to clinics for use by needy families. And the 93-year-old British prisoner of war whose life was saved by his magic tricks. Show less